1) The input of the model is
the grayscale image while the target output is the a*b* components
of the CIE L*a*b* colorspace.  The a*b* components are globally
normalized so they lie in the [0;1] range of the Sigmoid transfer
function. We then scale the target output to the size of the output
of the colorization network and compute the MSE between the output and
target output as the loss

